    {
      "id": "Hbol",
      "code_hash": "02b7eaffc1e311797eaae171c538dfe4",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"loss-landscape-visualization\">Loss Landscape Visualization</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><em>Based on a <a href=\"https://kindxiaoming.github.io/blog/2026/loss-visualization-1/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">blog post</a> by <a href=\"https://kindxiaoming.github.io/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Ziming Liu</a>.</em></span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Explore the <strong>local-plane</strong> method for visualizing 2D loss landscapes of neural\nnetworks, based on\n<a href=\"https://kindxiaoming.github.io/blog/2026/loss-visualization-1/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Ziming Liu's blog post</a>.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>The idea:</strong> Standard PCA projections of weight trajectories capture global\nstructure but miss local geometry. Instead, we build local 2D coordinate systems\nat each trajectory point using <strong>velocity</strong> (tangent) and <strong>acceleration</strong>\n(curvature) directions, then blend them with Gaussian weighting to produce a\nsmooth landscape.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Use the controls below to pick a target function, network architecture, and\nvisualization parameters, then watch the optimizer roll through the loss landscape.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "MJUe",
      "code_hash": "97f9cb66b04075014c3a4764c273646a",
